cast_shell: drop the unconditional --disable-gpu-early-init default

CastBrowserMainParts appends `--disable-gpu-early-init` to the
command line via kDefaultSwitches with the rationale "It's better to
start GPU process on demand. For example, for TV platforms cast
starts in background and can't render until TV switches to cast
input."

On bridgething there's no equivalent "user switches input" event;
the device boots straight into the kiosk with an active output and
needs to render immediately. With the switch on,
content/browser/browser_main_loop.cc takes the
gpu-channel-not-yet-established path:

  establish_gpu_channel = true;
  if (parsed_command_line_->HasSwitch(switches::kDisableGpu) ||
      parsed_command_line_->HasSwitch(switches::kDisableGpuCompositing) ||
      parsed_command_line_->HasSwitch(switches::kDisableGpuEarlyInit)) {
    establish_gpu_channel = always_uses_gpu = false;
  }
  BrowserGpuChannelHostFactory::Initialize(establish_gpu_channel);

`always_uses_gpu = false` plus the factory initialised without a
channel leaves the viz Display compositor without a GPU output
surface; frame production for the aura compositor never starts, so
WaylandFrameManager gets no frame with config.buffer_id != 0 after
the first xdg_surface.ack_configure and the wl_surface stays
unmapped. The empirical signature on this stack is a single
ack_configure followed by indefinite wayland silence with the panel
showing weston-desktop-shell's background.

Removing the entry lets the default browser-main-loop initialise the
GPU channel at startup the same way upstream chrome does, so viz
boots with a working output and the wayland buffer-attach loop
spins up immediately.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/browser/cast_browser_main_parts.cc
+++ b/chromecast/browser/cast_browser_main_parts.cc
@@ -331,10 +331,6 @@
 #endif
 #endif
 #endif  // BUILDFLAG(IS_LINUX) || BUILDFLAG(IS_CHROMEOS)
-    // It's better to start GPU process on demand. For example, for TV platforms
-    // cast starts in background and can't render until TV switches to cast
-    // input.
-    {switches::kDisableGpuEarlyInit, ""},
     // Enable navigator.connection API.
     // TODO(derekjchow): Remove this switch when enabled by default.
     {switches::kEnableNetworkInformationDownlinkMax, ""},
